CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1772175649
OL,3,CGreens confident as counting underway
OL,4,Cin Gorton and Denton
OL,6,FLabour won Gorton and Denton in 2024
OL,7,Fwith more than half the vote, but the
OL,8,Fmood at the count pointed to an uphill
OL,9,Fbattle for the party's candidate
OL,10,FAngeliki Stogia and a possible victory
OL,11,Ffor the Greens' Hannah Spencer.
OL,13,FIt would be the Greens' first ever
OL,14,Fvictory in a parliamentary by-
OL,15,Felection, with a party source
OL,16,Fpredicting a "seismic moment" in UK
OL,17,Fpolitics.
OL,19,FA Labour defeat in the party's long-
OL,20,Ftime stronghold would be a major blow
OL,21,Fto Sir Keir Starmer's leadership.
OL,26,@xD@NOUxD@]O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
