CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1772175649
OL,3,CGreens confident as counting underway
OL,4,Cin Gorton and Denton
OL,6,FLabour sought to pitch itself as the
OL,7,Fonly option for anti-Reform voters,
OL,8,Fbut a loss would undermine that claim
OL,9,Fin future elections and instead boost
OL,10,Fthe Greens' credibility on that front.
OL,12,FA Green Party source told the Press
OL,13,FAssociation: "Things are feeling
OL,14,Fpositive.
OL,16,F"Whatever happens, I think it's fair
OL,17,Fto say that Greens are here to stay
OL,18,Fnow as a progressive voice in British
OL,19,Fpolitics.
OL,26,@uD@NOUxD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30304
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1772175649
OL,3,CGreens confident as counting underway
OL,4,Cin Gorton and Denton
OL,6,F"I think it's a seismic moment in
OL,7,FBritish politics where Greens are
OL,8,Fshowing that they're a party that can
OL,9,Fprotect the country from the threat of
OL,10,FReform, and that Labour's not up to
OL,11,Fthe job."
OL,13,FLabour sources sounded more downbeat,
OL,14,Ftelling the Press Association: "Early
OL,15,Fsigns at the count indicate the Greens
OL,16,Fhave been able to turn out support in
OL,17,Fa way they wouldn't be able to
OL,18,Freplicate at a general election."
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@IO]vD@`OUzD@aO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/10
